        <!-- Section: Advantages -->
        <section id="advantages" class="content-section">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-sky-900 mb-4">Why Combine Liquid and Solid-State?</h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
                    Integrating liquid memory with solid-state modules allows a breakthrough in computing architecture. This hybrid approach directly solves the primary limitations of traditional solid-state drives.
                </p>
                
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                    <!-- Problem 1: Heat Buildup -->
                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">Problem: Heat Buildup üî•</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600">High-speed SSDs generate significant heat, leading to thermal throttling which reduces performance.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 p-6 md:col-span-2">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-800 mb-3">Solution: Superior Heat Transfer üßä</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600">The liquid memory medium and integrated thermal micro-pipes provide superior heat transfer, moving heat away from critical components to maintain peak stability and performance.</p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Problem 2: Wear Cycles -->
                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">Problem: Wear Cycles ‚è≥</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600">NAND flash memory has a finite number of write cycles, causing the drive to "wear out" over time, especially in write-heavy tasks.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 p-6 md:col-span-2">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-800 mb-3">Solution: Low-Wear Fluid States üîÑ</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600">Liquid memory channels operate with near-zero mechanical wear and feature self-healing molecular structures, offering exponentially longer endurance for write-intensive operations.</p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Problem 3: Speed Bottlenecks -->
                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">Problem: Speed Bottlenecks ‚ö°</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600">Traditional architectures are limited by data transfer speeds between separate memory and processing units.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rounded-lg bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 p-6 md:col-span-2">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-800 mb-3">Solution: Adaptive In-Memory Computation üß†</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600">The hybrid module enables adaptive computation possibilities directly within the memory, reducing latency and bypassing traditional bottlenecks for faster processing.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

